-- Abercrombie & Fitch April same-store sales up 6 pct
-- 
-- Thu May 8, 2008 8:13am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/05/08/us-usa-retailsales-abercrombie-idUSWNAS284620080508

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Apparel retailer Abercrombie & Fitch Co ( ANF.N ) said on Thursday its sales at stores open at least a year rose 6 percent in April. 

 Analysts, on average, had expected an increase of 2 percent, according to Reuters Estimates. The New Albany, Ohio-based company, which owns the Abercrombie & Fitch, Hollister and RUEHL chains, said net sales rose to $241.0 million for the four-week period ended May 3, from $204.6 million in the comparable period a year earlier. (Reporting by  Nicole Maestri )